race.comment: SON OF EUREKA (3) disappointed last start when well supported at Wagga but did make a mess of his maiden fresh in a dominant pillar-to-post win. Suspect he puts that run swiftly behind him. AIRLINER (8) bounced back to form last start when second at Moruya over 1200m, beaten half a length. Extra trip a plus. One of the main contenders. FLASHY ICON (4) scored a commanding win at Canberra Acton over 1900m when last sighted on June 6. This is short of a preferred trip but sets up as a good starting point. SEBASTIAN'S FLYER (10) simply got too far back around a noted frontrunners track last start. Resumed well at Wagga and much better suited at Nowra with its 400m straight.
